## $VER: DVI.guide v3.63 (07.07.94)


@node Main "DVI 3.63 Amiga online documentation"

Welcome to the DVI & DVILW 3.63 online documentation. DVI is a
previewer and printer driver for TeX dvi files. DVILW is a postscript
converter for dvi files. Select one of the following topics:

         @{" About DVI & DVILW    " link About}
         @{" Special requirements " link Requirements}
         @{" Installation         " link Installation}
         @{" Working with DVI     " link DVI}
         @{" Working with DVILW   " link DVILW}
         @{" Authors an updates   " link Authors}

DVI & DVILW are (C) 1994 by Ingo Eichenseher, Gerhard Wilhelms and
Markus Zahn.

DVI must not be included in a commercial public domain distribution
without the written permission of the authors.

Your fee is to report all occuring errors to the @{"authors" link
Authors}!

@endnode


@node About "About DVI & DVILW"

DVI is a TeX previewer with integrated printer drivers.
Supported printers are
o HP PCL compatible printers ( HP Laser- / Deskjets etc. ),
o NEC P6 compatible printers ( NEC P6, EPSON LQ, etc. )
o FX-80 compatible printers ( Epson FX-80, Star LC-10, etc. ) and
o Canon BJ-300 compatible printers.

DVILW is a postscript converter for dvi files.

Both programs support
o virtual fonts
o 2D und 3D graphics based on \special commands.

There are existing implementations for Amiga computers, Atari ST
computers, Apollo workstations, workstations with X11/Motif and IBM PC
compatibles.

@endnode


@node Requirements "Special requirements"

DVI requires AmigaOS Release 2.04 or higher (V37+). As always with TeX
and graphics the best configuration is 2MB memory or more and at least
1MB of chip memory.

DVILW should run on any AmigaOS. To use pattern matching with command
line arguments, AmigaOS 2.04 or higher (V37+) is required.

Both programs are able to use ARexx for automatic font generation.
ARexx is part of AmigaOS 2.04 or higher (V37+).

To use the online documentation, AmigaGuide is required. You need the
C= Installer to use the provided installation script. Both packages
should be available on any Aminet site.

Last but not least, TeX and Metafont should be installed properly :-)
     
@endnode


@node Installation "Installation"

Installation of DVI and DVILW is quite easy, using the provided
installer script. Simply follow the guidelines given.

To do a "by hand installation", you should:

o Copy the executable files Bin/dvi and Bin/dvilw to a directory of
  your choice. This directory should be added to your path. For PasTeX
  users, TeX:bin would be a good choice.
o Copy the configuration files Config/dvi.opt, Config/dvilw.opt,
  Config/dvilw.map and Config/dvilw.ps to TeX:config (PasTeX) or any
  directory specified with the environment variable TEXCONFIG.
o Optional, you can copy the ARexx script Rexx/MakePKFont.rexx to your
  REXX: directory.
o Change the copied files dvi.opt and dvilw.opt to your personal
  needs. See @{"DVI menus/Setup menu" link SetupMenu} for details. At
  least PKPATH should be set to your personal needs.
       
@endnode


@node DVI "Working with DVI"

DVI can be invoked from Workbench by a double click on its icon. As
TeX is very command line oriented, DVI will mostly be invoked from a
shell:

                     dvi [@{"options" link DVIOptions}] [dvifile]

If started from Workbench, the @{"options" link DVIOptions} are read from the Tooltypes of
the DVI program and dvi file icons. Permanent options can be set in the
configuration file dvi.opt in both cases.

When the DVI screen came up with its control window, you can use the
@{"Project menu" link ProjectMenu} to load a dvi file to preview. In addition, DVI adds an
entry to the Workbenchs Tools menu, so you can select and load a dvi
file from Workbench.

The @{"Screen menu" link ScreenMenu} is available to move around in the current dvi
document. The keyboard could be used for some actions, too. Press
ENTER to get to the next, or BACKSPACE to get to the previous page. To
scroll the current page, you can either drag the page with the mouse
( click into the current page and move the mouse while holding down
the left mouse button ) or use the cursor keys.

Print your dvi document or parts of it with the @{"Printer menu" link PrinterMenu}.

With the @{"Setup menu" link SetupMenu}, you are able to configure DVI for your personal
needs.

@endnode


@node DVIOptions "DVI Options"

CALLMF=name          - Name of the ARexx script for automatic font
                       generation: ( e.g. Rexx:MakePKFont.rexx )
COPIES=n             - Number of copies for printing.
DENSITY=dens         - Value of darkness for IMG graphics;
                       Between 0.0 and 1.0.
EJECT=on/off         - Formfeed after each page while printing?
HEIGHT=dimen         - Page height.
HMARGIN=dimen        - Horizontal margin.
HOFFSET=dimen        - Horizontal offset.
HRESOLUTION=dpi      - Horizontal screen resolution in dpi.
HSPREAD=dimen        - Horizontal spread.
IMGPATH=path         - Search path for graphic files.
LANDSCAPE=on/off     - Landscape output?
LOGFILE=name         - Name of the logfile; If empty, no logfile will be
                       created.
MAGNIFICATION=mag    - Magnification.
MEMORY=on/off        - Hold current dvi file in memory?
OUTPUT=printer       - Kind of printer: fx80, p6low, p6mid, p6high,
                       hplow, hphigh, or bj300.
PATH=path            - Search path for dvi files.
PATHMEM=n            - Maximum memory for graphic commands.
PICTURES=on/off      - Show pictures?
PIXMEM=n             - Maximum memory for printer bitmap.
PKPATH=path          - Path and name od the pk font files.
REDIRECT=name        - Name of a redirection file for printing.
SCREENMODE=name,cols - DisplayMode name (like in Prefs/ScreenMode) and 
                       number of desired colors ( 2 or 4 )
SEPARATE=on/off      - Printout quality.
SHOWFONTS=on/off     - Show protocol of used fonts.
SINGLESHEET=on/off   - Request for new sheet of paper after each printed
                       page.
TFMPATH=path         - Search path for tfm files.
THINOUT=on/off       - Thinout output.
TRACECHARS=on/off    - Show protocol of printed characters?
TRACEMEM=on/off      - Show protocol of used memory?
VFPATH=path          - Search path for virtual fonts.
VMARGIN=dimen        - Vertical margin.
VOFFSET=dimen        - Vertical offset.
VRESOLUTION=dpi      - Vertical screen resolution in dpi.
VSPREAD=dimen        - Vertical spread.
WIDTH=dimen          - Page width.

@endnode


@node ProjectMenu "The Project menu"

The following items are available in the Project menu:

Load DVI...  - With this item, you can select a dvi file to display.
Update DVI   - You can reload the current dvi file with this item.
Save options - This choice saves the current options to dvi.opt.
About...     - Would you like to see some information about DVI?
Quit         - Are you sure to quit DVI?

@endnode


@node ScreenMenu "The Screen menu"

The following items are available in the Screen menu:

Next Page        - Move to the next page. Pressing the 'Return' or 'Enter'
                   key moves you to the next page, too.
Previous Page    - Move to the previous page. Pressing the 'Backspace' key
                   moves you to the previous page, too.
Goto Page...     - Specify a pagenumber to jump to.
Magnification... - Specify the display magnification.

@endnode


@node PrinterMenu "The Printer menu"

The following items are available in the Printer menu:

Print Range... - Specify and print a range of the current document.
Print Page     - Print current page of the current document.
Print Document - Print the current document (all pages).

@endnode


@node SetupMenu "The Setup menu"

The following items are available in the Setup menu:

Directories... - Set the correct directories of your TeX installation with
                 this item:
                 PK  Path - Template for the PK font paths and names.
                            %d = actual font resolution in dpi
                            %h = horizontal base resolution in dpi
                            %m = actual magstep (MAG___1.2 etc.)
                            %s = font name (cmr10 etc.)
                            %v = vertical base resolution in dpi
                            A template like TeX:pk/%d/%s.%dpk generates font
                            names/path like TeX:pk/110/cmr10.110pk.
                 TFM Path - Specify the correct path of the TFM files here.
                 IMG Path - Set the path to be searched for IMG graphics.
                 GR  Path - Search path for graphics files included with
                            \special{gr input ...}
                 VF  Path - Set the search path for virtual font files here.
                 Call MF  - Path and name of the ARexx script to be called
                            in the case of automatic font generation.
Margins...     - Specify the desired margins and offsets here.
Options        - Toggle some options with this item:
                 Eject       - Paperfeed after each page on/off.
                 Landscape   - Print pages in landscape mode?
                 Memory      - Hold current dvi file completely in memory?
                 Pictures    - Show IMG graphics?
                 Separate    - Control print quality.
                 Showfonts   - Show protocol of used fonts on/off.
                 Singlesheet - Request paper after each page?
                 Thinout     - Thinout output on/off.
                 Tracechars  - Show protocol of used charcters?
                 Tracemem    - Show protocol of used memory?
Printer...     - Specify the connected printer here:
                 NEC P6 low             - 180 x 180 dpi
                 NEC P6 high            - 360 x 360 dpi
                 NEC P6 mid             - 360 x 180 dpi
                 Epson FX-80            - 240 x 216 dpi
                 HP Desk-/Laserjet high - 300 x 300 dpi
                 HP Desk-/Laserjet low  - 100 x 100 dpi
                 Canon BJ-300           - 300 x 300 dpi
Screenmode...  - Choose an acceptable screenmode for DVI with this item.
                 This item is only available with Amiga OS 2.1 or
                 higher (V38+).

@endnode


@node DVILW "Working with DVILW"

DVILW can be invoked from Workbench by a double click on its icon. As
TeX is very command line oriented, DVILW will mostly be invoked from a
shell:

dvilw [@{"options" link DVILWOptions}] <dvifiles>

Permanent options can be set in the configuration file dvi.opt in both
cases. Due to the 1-1 port of the Unix DVILW sources, DVILW reads the
Workbench Tooltypes of neither the DVI program icon nor the dvi file icon.

Use the following variables to change the configuration file dvilw.opt to
your personal needs:

CALLMF=name        - Name of the ARexx script for automatic font
                     generation: ( e.g. Rexx:MakePKFont.rexx )
COPIES=n           - Number of copies for printing.
DENSITY=dens       - Value of darkness for IMG graphics;
                     Between 0.0 and 1.0.
DVIPATH=path       - Search path for dvi files.
GRPATH=path        - Search path for graphics files include with the
                     \special{gr input ...} command
HMARGIN=dimen      - Horizontal margin.
HRESOLUTION=dpi    - Horizontal screen resolution in dpi.
IMGPATH=path       - Search path for graphic files.
LANDSCAPE=on/off   - Landscape output?
MAGNIFICATION=mag  - Magnification.
MAXMEM             - Specify the maximum amount of used memory
MEMORY=on/off      - Hold current dvi file in memory?
PATH=path          - Search path for dvi files.
PKPATH=path        - Path and name od the pk font files.
                     See @{"Setup/Directories" link SetupMenu} for details.
PSPATH=path        - Search path of postscript files included with the
                     \special{ps ...} command
SHOWFONTS=on/off   - Show protocol of used fonts.
TFMPATH=path       - Search path for tfm files.
TRACEMEM=on/off    - Show protocol of used memory?
VFPATH=path        - Search path for virtual fonts.
VMARGIN=dimen      - Vertical margin.
VRESOLUTION=dpi    - Vertical screen resolution in dpi.

@endnode


@node DVILWOptions "DVILW Options"

Due to the 1-1 port of the Unix DVILW sources, DVILW accepts its options
only in a non Amiga format, like -o etc. The following options are
available:

-o <list>               list of pages to print.
                        -o 4      -> print page number 4
                        -o 9-12   -> print pages 9 to 12
                        -o 4,9-12 -> print pages 4, 9, 10, 11 and 12
                        Alternatively:
                        -o start:stop
                        -o start:stop:step
                        -o range:step
-b <n>                  first page to print
-e <n>                  last page to print
-c <n>                  print a number of n copies
-y                      CR+LF instead of LF at end of postscript line
-m <mag>                magnification, 1000 = original value,
                        1200 = magnification of factor 1.2, etc.
-f <path>               similar to the PKPATH variable
-g <path>               similar to the IMGPATH variable
-q                      similar to the SHOWFONTS variable
-r                      output of pages in reverse order
-u                      output of pages in physical order
-a <name>, -p <name>    name of the postscript output file
-h <dimen>              move the output page to the right (dimen>0) or to
                        the left (dimen<0). dimen is a TeX value, like 1pt,
                        2.7cm, etc.
-v <dimen>              move the output page up (dimen<0) or down (dimen>0)
                        dimen is a TeX value like 1pt, 1.2cm, etc.
-zr <integer>           printer resolution in dpi, default: 300
-zt <path>              similar to the TFMPATH variable
-t                      print to stdout
-k <filename>           select alternative prolog file
-l                      select landscape output

@endnode


